[2026-07-13T17:53:58.570Z] [INFO]         "tool_use_id": "toolu_01WNg8R41ruNNstPwtuUqpWL",
[2026-07-13T17:53:58.570Z] [INFO]         "type": "tool_result",
[2026-07-13T17:53:58.570Z] [INFO]         "content": "title:\tE36: Hive-Mind-dispatched end-to-end issue solve by Formal AI\nstate:\tOPEN\nauthor:\tkonard (Konstantin Diachenko)\nlabels:\t\ncomments:\t1\nassignees:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nissue-type:\t\nparent:\tlink-assistant/formal-ai#651\nsub-issues:\t\nsub-issues-completed:\t\nblocked-by:\tlink-assistant/formal-ai#654\nblocking:\tlink-assistant/formal-ai#657\nnumber:\t655\n--\nParent: #651. Full planning context with audits: `docs/case-studies/issue-651/` (this issue is E36 in `proposed-issues.md` there; added by PR #652).\n\n\n**Problem**\n\nThe self-coding rung 2 in `VISION.md` requires a real loop: Hive Mind\n(`solve <issue-url> --tool agent --model formal-ai`) drives the Agent CLI,\nwhich drives `formal-ai serve --agent-mode`, and the session takes a small,\nwell-specified repository issue from plan to draft PR. Today every piece\nexists separately — Agent CLI ships Formal AI as a built-in provider\n(`docs/formal-ai.md` in link-assistant/agent; base URL\n`http://127.0.0.1:8080/api/openai/v1`), Hive Mind passes `--model formal-ai`\nthrough unchanged (`src/agent.lib.mjs`, `agentModels[model] || model`) — but\nno recorded end-to-end run exists, so the claim is unverified.\n\n**Approach**\n\n1. Author a scripted scenario under `examples/self-coding/`: a scratch\n   repository with one small issue (e.g. add a missing plural surface to a\n   seed meaning — the issue #538 atomic-edit shape), a `formal-ai serve\n   --agent-mode` instance, the Agent CLI, and the Hive Mind `solve` entry.\n2. Capture the full session: Hive Mind logs, Agent CLI `--output-format\n   stream-json` events, the Formal AI event log, and the resulting branch\n   diff, stored under `docs/case-studies/issue-651/self-coding-run/`.\n3. Add a CI job (or extend `test-agent-cli-e2e`) that replays the bounded\n   inner loop (Agent CLI ↔ Formal AI, no GitHub access) deterministically.\n4. Report upstream gaps discovered along the way as issues on\n   link-assistant/agent and link-assistant/hive-mind (e.g. adding `formal-ai`\n   to `agentModels` in `src/models/index.mjs`).\n5. Document the recipe in `CONTRIBUTING.md` as the standard self-coding\n   verification path.\n\n**Existing components**\n\n- `formal-ai serve --agent-mode` + `FORMAL_AI_API_BEARER_TOKEN`;\n  `GET /health`, `GET /api/openai/v1/models`.\n- Agent CLI provider selectors `formal-ai`, `formalai/formal-ai`; env\n  `FORMAL_AI_API_KEY`, `FORMAL_AI_BASE_URL`.\n- Hive Mind `solve.mjs` / `src/agent.lib.mjs` (validates with\n  `printf \"hi\" | agent --model <m>`).\n- `scripts/reproduce-issue-538.sh` and the session JSONs under\n  `docs/case-studies/issue-538/` — the bounded replay precedent.\n\n**Acceptance criteria**\n\n- A committed, replayable session under\n  `docs/case-studies/issue-651/self-coding-run/` shows issue text in → draft\n  branch diff out, with every step present in the Formal AI event log.\n- `cargo test self_coding_session_replays` (or an e2e script in CI) replays\n  the inner Agent-CLI ↔ Formal-AI exchange byte-for-byte offline.\n- The scratch-issue diff passes the scenario's own verification command\n  (its `cargo test` / seed parity check).\n- `CONTRIBUTING.md` documents the end-to-end command sequence.\n\n\n\n=== PR ===\ntitle:\tAdd replayable Hive Mind self-coding verification\nstate:\tDRAFT\nauthor:\tkonard (Konstantin Diachenko)\nlabels:\t\nassignees:\tkonard (Konstantin Diachenko)\nreviewers:\t\nprojects:\t\nmilestone:\t\nnumber:\t679\nurl:\thttps://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/679\nadditions:\t917\ndeletions:\t73\nauto-merge:\tdisabled\n--\n## Summary\n\n- Integrates the green general-planner foundation from #677 and adds a scratch-repository self-coding scenario under `examples/self-coding/`.\n- Captures real Agent CLI stream events, Formal AI request traces, the generated plan, deterministic session JSON, and the resulting verified diff.\n- Adds byte-for-byte offline replay coverage and runs the scenario in the existing real Agent CLI E2E job.\n- Documents the standard command sequence in `CONTRIBUTING.md`.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n```bash\ncargo build --release --bin formal-ai\nexamples/self-coding/run.sh\ncargo test self_coding_session_replays\n```\n\nThe scratch issue requests `self-coding-result.txt` containing `self-coding=passed`; the captured diff and verification command prove the change completed.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `cargo test`: 1,519 passed, 2 ignored\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- real Agent CLI ↔ Formal AI replay: 183 valid stream-JSON events\n- changed-file size thresholds checked directly (`rust-script` is unavailable locally)\n\n## Upstream gap discovered\n\nThe required outer command, `solve ISSUE_URL --tool agent --model formal-ai`, is rejected by Hive Mind 2.5.2 before Agent CLI starts because `formal-ai` is absent from its validation map. The real dispatch failure is committed in the case study and tracked as [link-assistant/hive-mind#2059](https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/2059). The deterministic inner Agent CLI ↔ Formal AI loop is complete and CI-replayable; the outer live entry remains gated by that upstream fix.\n\nFixes #655",
